Philippine Stocks: DMCI Holdings, Philex Mining

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-07T04:29:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/philippine-stocks-dmci-holdings-philex-mining-san-miguel.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in Manila.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 0.2 percent to
4,219.43, the highest since Dec. 8.  DMCI Holdings Inc. (DMC)  , the nation’s biggest
construction company, rose 1 percent to 39.45 pesos, the highest
since March 18, after the company signed a contract to build a
power plant and the Philippine Daily Inquirer said the company’s
residential unit is targeting a 20 percent increase in home
sales this year, citing Joseph Ramil Lombos, the venture’s
director for finance. DMCI President Isidro Consunji wasn’t in
his office, an official said when Bloomberg News called for
comment.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , the largest Philippine metals
producer, advanced 2.1 percent to 15.90 pesos, the highest close
since Jan. 19, after gold prices rose to a record for a second
day yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in  Manila  at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
